docs.lead_paragraph: WASHINGTON — Focusing squarely on his ties to President Trump, federal prosecutors argued Wednesday that Roger J. Stone Jr. blatantly obstructed a congressional investigation into Russian interference in the 2016 election because the truth “would look really bad” for Mr. Trump.

docs.lead_paragraph: Washington loves a spectacle, even if Robert S. Mueller III was determined not to make one. On Wednesday, as Mr. Mueller was finally slated to testify in two back-to-back House hearings about his conclusions as special counsel, anticipation coursed through the halls of Capitol Hill.

docs.abstract: A federal loan forgiveness program made a promise to students: Stick with your vital but low-wage professions and your debts will be wiped clean. Then they weren’t.
docs.snippet: A federal loan forgiveness program made a promise to students: Stick with your vital but low-wage professions and your debts will be wiped clean. Then they weren’t.
docs.lead_paragraph: WASHINGTON — When Congress created a student loan forgiveness program in 2007, lawmakers wanted to draw people to vital but relatively low-paid careers with a promise: after a decade, if borrowers faithfully paid their debts and pursued their work, they would have the remainder of their student loans written off.

headline.main: Broken Promises and Debt Pile Up as Loan Forgiveness Goes Astray
headline.print_headline: Promises Fade  As Debts Surge  For Graduates

byline.original: By Erica L. Green and Stacy Cowley

docs.abstract: A federal judge said the education secretary had violated an order to stop collecting on loans owed by students from a now-defunct for-profit chain of colleges.
docs.snippet: A federal judge said the education secretary had violated an order to stop collecting on loans owed by students from a now-defunct for-profit chain of colleges.
docs.lead_paragraph: WASHINGTON — A federal judge on Thursday fined Education Secretary Betsy DeVos for contempt of court, ruling that she had violated an order to stop collecting on loans owed by students from a now-defunct for-profit chain of colleges.

headline.main: Betsy DeVos Is Held in Contempt Over Judge’s Order on Loan Collection
headline.print_headline: DeVos Held In Contempt For Collecting Student Loans

byline.original: By Erica L. Green and Stacy Cowley

docs.abstract: Steven Menashi, who faces a key vote Thursday, helped devise an Education Department plan to use Social Security data to deny students debt relief, an effort that a judge ruled violated privacy laws.
docs.snippet: Steven Menashi, who faces a key vote Thursday, helped devise an Education Department plan to use Social Security data to deny students debt relief, an effort that a judge ruled violated privacy laws.
docs.lead_paragraph: WASHINGTON — A judicial nominee slated for a key Senate committee vote on Thursday helped devise an illegal Education Department effort to use private Social Security data to deny debt relief to thousands of students cheated by their for-profit colleges, according to a memo obtained by The New York Times.

headline.main: Appeals Court Nominee Shaped DeVos’s Illegal Loan Forgiveness Effort
headline.print_headline: Appeals Court Nominee  Shaped an Illegal Plan On Student Loan Relief

docs.abstract: The students were in the cross-fire of a regulatory fight between teachers unions and the Education Department.
docs.snippet: The students were in the cross-fire of a regulatory fight between teachers unions and the Education Department.
docs.lead_paragraph: WASHINGTON — Tens of thousands of students in California enrolled in online classes at out-of-state colleges abruptly lost federal financial aid this week after they found themselves in the cross-fire of a regulatory fight between Education Secretary Betsy DeVos and the nation’s largest teachers’ union.

headline.main: Thousands of California Students Lose Financial Aid in Regulatory Fight
headline.print_headline: Regulatory Fight Shuts Off Aid for California Students in Online Classes

docs.snippet: A House committee has a trove of documents that show top Education Department officials trying to prop up a for-profit chain as it careened toward collapse.
docs.lead_paragraph: WASHINGTON — Dream Center Education Holdings, a subsidiary of a Los Angeles-based megachurch, had no experience in higher education when it petitioned the federal Education Department to let it take over a troubled chain of for-profit trade schools.

headline.main: Emails Show DeVos Aides Pulled Strings for Failing For-Profit Colleges

docs.abstract: A lawsuit against Holland Christian High School has turned Betsy DeVos’s alma mater into Exhibit A as the education secretary moves to lighten the rules governing school sexual assault.
docs.snippet: A lawsuit against Holland Christian High School has turned Betsy DeVos’s alma mater into Exhibit A as the education secretary moves to lighten the rules governing school sexual assault.
docs.lead_paragraph: WASHINGTON — If there was any school where her daughter would feel safe, Michelle Hoffman thought, it would be Holland Christian High School. Betsy DeVos, the famously religious education secretary, was educated there, and the school preached that its students would seek “in all endeavors to ‘do justice, love kindness, and walk humbly with their God.’”

headline.main: As DeVos Eases Sexual Assault Rules, Her Old High School May Provide a Test Case
headline.print_headline: DeVos’s Former School May Provide Test Case For Sexual Assault Rule

docs.abstract: Education Secretary Betsy DeVos formally repealed an Obama-era regulation that would have forced for-profit colleges to prove their debt-laden graduates could find gainful employment.
docs.snippet: Education Secretary Betsy DeVos formally repealed an Obama-era regulation that would have forced for-profit colleges to prove their debt-laden graduates could find gainful employment.
docs.lead_paragraph: Education Secretary Betsy DeVos on Friday officially repealed an Obama-era regulation that sought to crack down on for-profit colleges and universities that produced graduates with no meaningful job prospects and mountains of student debt they could not hope to repay.

headline.main: DeVos Repeals Obama-Era Rule Cracking Down on For-Profit Colleges
headline.print_headline: Rules on For-Profit Schools Are Repealed

docs.abstract: A manager in the White House’s Personnel Security Office said administration officials granted clearances to at least 25 people whose applications had been denied by career employees.
docs.snippet: A manager in the White House’s Personnel Security Office said administration officials granted clearances to at least 25 people whose applications had been denied by career employees.
docs.lead_paragraph: WASHINGTON — A whistle-blower working inside the White House has told a House committee that senior Trump administration officials granted security clearances to at least 25 individuals whose applications had been denied by career employees for “disqualifying issues” that could put national security at risk, the committee’s Democratic staff said Monday.

headline.main: White House Whistle-Blower Tells Congress of Irregularities in Security Clearances
headline.print_headline: New Questions  On Clearances  In White House
